data.title: Skinner, Cornelia Otis
data.meta_description: Born in Chicago on May 30, 1899, she was an actress and writer, known for The Uninvited (1944), The Pleasure of His Company (1961) and The Girl in the Red Velvet Swing (1955). She died in New York city on July 9, 1975. Signed inscription on 3 x 5 card. Very Good condition.
